enttyp.enttypd: Air quality monitoring sites in EPA Region 9 which monitored ozone (O3) during the 2012-2014 time period.

attr.attrdef: Internal feature number.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Name of state
Name of county
Nine digit numeric code which is a contatenation of state and county FIPS codes, and a four digit site code
Pollutant occurence code
Monitoring site name assigned by state or local agency
Physical street address of monitoring site

2012-2014 8-hour ozone design value; statistic that describes the air quality status of a monitor relative to the level of the 8-hour ozone National Ambient Air Quality Standards (NAAQS); expressed in parts per million
Validity of design value, based on level of data completeness
Completeness of ozone data for 2012, expressed as a percent
Completeness of ozone data for 2013, expressed as a percent
Completeness of ozone data for 2014, expressed as a percent
Completeness of ozone data for the 2012-2014 consecutive three-year period, expressed as a percent
Number of days in 2012 that the monitor exceeded the 2008 8-hour ozone standard of 0.075 ppm
Number of days in 2013 that the monitor exceeded the 2008 8-hour ozone standard of 0.075 ppm
Number of days in 2014 that the monitor exceeded the 2008 8-hour ozone standard of 0.075 ppm
The fourth-highest daily maximum 8-hour concentration recorded by the monitor in 2012; expressed in parts per million (ppm)
The fourth-highest daily maximum 8-hour concentration recorded by the monitor in 2013; expressed in parts per million (ppm)
The fourth-highest daily maximum 8-hour concentration recorded by the monitor in 2014; expressed in parts per million (ppm)
Latitude of monitor coordinate
Longitude of monitor coordiante
Feature geometry.
